chat.Mark Description:
The current mark function is a beta version.

After clicking to add a mark, you need to select a knowledge base to store the mark data. You can use this function to quickly mark questions and expected answers to guide the model's answers next time.

Currently, like other data in the knowledge base, the marking function is affected by the model and does not represent 100% compliance with expectations after marking.

The marked data is only unidirectionally synchronized with the knowledge base. If the knowledge base modifies the marked data, the marked data displayed in the log cannot be synchronized.

search.Empty result response Tips: If this is filled, when no suitable content is found, the filled content will be directly replied.

search.Min Similarity Tips: Relevance differs for different index models, please use search tests to select an appropriate value. When using ReRank, the relevance may be very low.
search.No support similarity: Relevance filtering is only supported when using result reranking or semantic search
search.ReRank desc: Use a reranking model for secondary sorting to enhance overall ranking.

mode.embedding desc: Use vectors for text relevance queries
mode.fullTextRecall desc: Use traditional full-text search, suitable for finding data with specific keywords and subject-predicate combinations
mode.mixedRecall desc: Return the combined results of vector search and full-text search, ranked using the RRF algorithm.

score.embedding desc: Calculate the score by computing the distance between vectors, range 0~1.
score.fullText desc: Calculate the score of matching keywords, range 0~infinity.
score.reRank desc: Calculate the relevance between sentences using a ReRank model, range 0~1.
score.rrf desc: Merge multiple search results by calculating inverted rankings.

training.Auto mode Tip: Increase the semantic richness of data chunks through sub-indexes and calling models to generate related questions and summaries, which is more conducive to retrieval. Requires more storage space and increases AI invocations.

description.Background: You can add introductions to specific content for better identification of user question types. This content is usually used to introduce something the model doesn't know.
description.Http Request Header:
Custom request headers, please fill in strict JSON string.
1. Ensure the last property has no comma
2. Ensure keys are wrapped in double quotes
For example: {"Authorization":"Bearer xxx"}
description.Http Request Url: New HTTP request URL. If there are two "Request URLs", you can delete the module and add it again to fetch the latest module configuration.
description.Response content:

Non-string type data will be automatically converted to string when passed in

description.Trigger:
Most of the time, you don't need to connect this attribute.

description.dynamic input: Receives dynamically added parameters from users, these parameters will be flattened and passed in at runtime
description.textEditor textarea: Variables passed in can be referenced using {{key}}. Variables only support strings or numbers.

placeholder.Classify background:
For example:
1. AIGC (AI-Generated Content) refers to automatically or semi-automatically generating digital content such as text, images, music, videos, etc. using artificial intelligence technology.
2. AIGC technology includes but is not limited to natural language processing, computer vision, machine learning, and deep learning. These technologies can create new content or modify existing content to meet specific creative, educational, entertainment, or informational needs.

description.Ai response content: Will be triggered after stream reply is complete
description.New context: Concatenates the current reply content with the history and returns it as the new context

description.query extension result: Outputs as a string array, this result can be directly connected to the "User Question" of "Knowledge Base Search", it is recommended not to connect it to the "User Question" of "AI Conversation"

template.AI response switch tip: If you want the current node not to output content, you can turn off this switch. The content output by AI will not be shown to the user, you can manually perform special processing using "AI Reply Content".
template.AI support tool tip: Models that support function calling can better utilize tool invocations.
template.Assigned reply intro: This module can directly reply with a specified piece of content. Commonly used for guidance and prompts. Non-string content will be converted to string for output when passed in.
template.Chat entrance intro: When a user sends content, the flow will start executing from this module.
template.Classify question intro:
Determine the type of the current question based on the user's history and current question. Multiple sets of question types can be added, here is a template example:
Type 1: Greeting
Type 2: Questions about product "usage"
Type 3: Questions about product "purchase"
Type 4: Other questions
template.Dataset search intro: Invokes knowledge base search capability to find content that may be relevant to the question
template.Dataset search result concat intro: Can merge and output multiple knowledge base search results. Uses the RRF merging method for final ranking and output.
template.Extract field intro: Can extract specified data from text, such as: SQL statements, search keywords, code, etc.
template.Http request intro: Can send an HTTP request to implement more complex operations (online search, database query, etc.)
template.Query extension intro: Using the question optimization feature can improve the accuracy of knowledge base searches during continuous dialogue. When this feature is used, AI will first construct one or more new search terms based on the context, which are more conducive to knowledge base search. This module is built into the knowledge base search module, if you only perform a single knowledge base search, you can directly use the built-in completion function of the knowledge base.
template.Running app intro: Can select another application to invoke
template.TFSwitch intro: Outputs True or False based on the input content. By default, when the input content is false, undefined, null, 0, none, it will output false. You can also add some custom strings to supplement content that outputs false. Non-string, non-number, non-boolean types directly output True.
template.textEditor intro: Can process fixed or input text and then output, non-string type data will ultimately be converted to string type.
